    <h2 id="why-magnesium">Why Magnesium Gummies Matter for Sleep and Recovery</h2>

    <p>Magnesium is involved in over 300 enzymatic reactions in the human body, including muscle contraction, nerve transmission, protein synthesis, and — critically for this guide — the regulation of sleep-wake cycles and stress hormones. Despite its fundamental importance, magnesium deficiency is remarkably widespread in the American population, driven by declining soil mineral content, processed food consumption, and chronic stress that depletes magnesium stores.</p>

