      <p class="key-stat-txt">of Americans do not meet the Recommended Dietary Allowance for magnesium, according to data from the <strong>National Institutes of Health</strong>. Subclinical deficiency is even higher, as standard blood tests measure serum magnesium (only 1% of body stores) and frequently miss intracellular depletion.</p>
    </div>

    <p>The gummy format has made magnesium supplementation significantly more accessible, particularly for individuals who find large magnesium tablets difficult to swallow or who experience nausea with capsules taken on an empty stomach. For enhanced relaxation, many users pair magnesium with <a href="/sleep/l-theanine-gummies/">L-theanine gummies</a> for alpha-wave-driven calm, or stack it with <a href="/sleep/gaba-gummies/">GABA gummies</a> to target the brain's primary inhibitory neurotransmitter directly. However, the form of magnesium inside the gummy matters far more than the gummy itself.</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
